---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import siteData from '../data/site.json';

const page = siteData.pages.work;
const styles = [
  'assets/css/tokens.css',
  'assets/css/interior-base.css',
  'assets/css/layout.css',
  'assets/css/components.css',
  'assets/css/services.css',
  'assets/css/lab.css',
];
---
<Base
  title={page.title}
  description={page.description}
  eyebrow={page.eyebrow}
  introKicker={page.introKicker}
  introTitle={page.introTitle}
  introText={page.introText}
  canonical={page.canonical}
  currentNav={page.currentNav}
  brandMode="editorial"
  styles={styles}
>
  <section class="section-block section-block--reading services-premise">
    <article class="card editorial-card stack">
      <p class="card-kicker">Founder-led practice</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Identity, language, and machinery built together.</h2>
      <p class="section-copy section-copy--large">Christopher Sandbatch leads a small number of engagements across agentic marketing, editorial strategy, writing, and web production. The work begins with the character of the project, then builds the public language and technical system required to carry it.</p>
      <p class="section-copy">This is not a content mill or a general-purpose agency. Strategy and execution remain in the same hands, from the first model of an audience to the last line of copy or code.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block services-section" aria-labelledby="services-offers-title">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="card-kicker">What can be commissioned</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading" id="services-offers-title">Four principal forms of work</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="section-grid section-grid--two services-grid">
      <article class="card service-card">
        <h3>Persona &amp; agentic marketing systems</h3>
        <p>Marketing systems built around memorable characters, explicit audience models, and agents that can act without dissolving the voice into automated sludge.</p>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Persona systems and audience architecture</li>
          <li>Agent roles, memory, prompts, and review controls</li>
          <li>Campaign concepts, voice systems, and operating playbooks</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card service-card">
        <h3>Websites &amp; digital publishing</h3>
        <p>Editorial and institutional websites in which art direction, copy, information architecture, and implementation belong to one coherent idea.</p>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Website design and front-end development</li>
          <li>Publication, archive, catalog, and commerce structures</li>
          <li>Accessible, maintainable deployment systems</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card service-card">
        <h3>Editing &amp; narrative architecture</h3>
        <p>Developmental editing and strategic language work for manuscripts, brands, and institutions with something difficult to say.</p>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Structural and developmental editing</li>
          <li>Positioning, messaging, and brand voice</li>
          <li>Publishing programs and editorial architecture</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article class="card service-card">
        <h3>Writing, research &amp; special projects</h3>
        <p>Long-form work that requires synthesis, cultural judgment, and a voice capable of carrying more than a list of findings.</p>
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Essays, reports, scripts, and commissioned research</li>
          <li>Historical and cultural synthesis</li>
          <li>Launch narratives and unusual editorial commissions</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block advanced-service" aria-labelledby="advanced-service-title">
    <article class="card quiet-panel stack">
      <p class="card-kicker">Advanced systems</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading" id="advanced-service-title">When the project has become too complicated to reason about.</h2>
      <p class="section-copy section-copy--large">For content, research, and AI systems that need explicit definitions and inspectable relationships, the practice also undertakes ontology, taxonomy, agent-memory, provenance, and review design.</p>
      <div class="tag-row" aria-label="Advanced system capabilities">
        <span class="tag">Ontology &amp; taxonomy</span>
        <span class="tag">Knowledge architecture</span>
        <span class="tag">Auditable AI workflows</span>
        <span class="tag">Provenance &amp; governance</span>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block service-evidence" aria-labelledby="service-evidence-title">
    <div class="section-header">
      <p class="card-kicker">Proof of practice</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading" id="service-evidence-title">Systems already made public, or sold.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="evidence-grid">
      <article class="card case-study">
        <p class="case-study__label">Recent client work / 2026</p>
        <h3>Hermes: persona-based agentic marketing</h3>
        <p>A complete marketing framework organized around personas: distinct roles, voices, relationships, memory, and human review rather than a single generic automation layer.</p>
        <p>The framework was acquired by a client. Client identity and implementation details remain private; the underlying capability is available for new, independently designed engagements.</p>
      </article>
      <div class="selected-work">
        <a class="work-link" href="/">
          <span>St. Expedite Press</span>
          <small>Identity, editorial system, website, commerce, and communications infrastructure</small>
        </a>
        <a class="work-link" href="https://st-expedite-press.github.io/rice-magazine/">
          <span>RICE Magazine</span>
          <small>Independent magazine identity, static publication system, and editorial image architecture</small>
        </a>
        <a class="work-link" href="https://ecoamericana.substack.com/">
          <span>Ecologica Americana</span>
          <small>Long-form writing, audience formation, cultural research, and public voice</small>
        </a>
        <a class="work-link" href="/books">
          <span>Books &amp; publishing</span>
          <small>Writing, editing, production, catalog strategy, and direct publication</small>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-grid section-grid--two lab-overview" aria-labelledby="lab-instrument-title">
    <article class="card stack">
      <p class="card-kicker">The Lab</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading" id="lab-instrument-title">American Anglossic Compass</h2>
      <p class="section-copy">Forty prompts across five axes. Seven archetypes. A scored sequence that resolves into an interpretive profile. The order shuffles fresh on each run. Local save state holds your position. Results open after completion, with an optional email gate.</p>
      <p class="section-copy">The Compass is a field instrument for what remains of the Anglossic tradition: an attempt to map the political and aesthetic topography that the contemporary moment has mostly lost the vocabulary for. It does not explain itself in advance. The prompts require interpretive judgment. Hold the ones that need more time.</p>
      <div class="tag-row">
        <span class="tag">Local save state</span>
        <span class="tag">Held prompts</span>
        <span class="tag">Result gate optional</span>
      </div>
      <div class="actions">
        <button class="button" id="compass-launch" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="compass-modal">Open the Compass</button>
      </div>
    </article>
    <aside class="card stack">
      <h2 class="section-heading">What to expect</h2>
      <ul class="meta-list">
        <li>Forty prompts across five axes resolve through seven archetypes.</li>
        <li>The order shuffles on each fresh run, and local save state holds your position.</li>
        <li>You can hold prompts that need more time, and results open after completion with an optional email gate.</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section-block section-block--reading engagement-panel" aria-labelledby="engagement-title">
    <article class="card quiet-panel stack">
      <p class="card-kicker">Engagement model</p>
      <h2 class="section-heading" id="engagement-title">A small number of projects, scoped around an outcome.</h2>
      <p class="section-copy section-copy--large">Use Connect to describe the problem, the desired result, what already exists, and whether you need strategy, execution, or both.</p>
      <ul class="engagement-list">
        <li><strong>Direct:</strong> work is led by Christopher Sandbatch, without account layers.</li>
        <li><strong>Selective:</strong> one or two substantial engagements are taken at a time.</li>
        <li><strong>Defined:</strong> projects are scoped by deliverables and decisions, not indefinite activity.</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="actions">
        <a class="button" href="/connect?about=general">Discuss a project</a>
        <a class="button-secondary" href="/about">Read the premise</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <Fragment slot="afterMain">
    <div class="lab-modal" id="compass-modal" hidden>
      <div class="card lab-dialog" id="compass-dialog" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="compass-title" tabindex="-1">
        <div class="lab-shell">
          <div class="lab-meta">
            <div>
              <p class="page-intro__kicker">Field instrument</p>
              <h2 class="section-heading" id="compass-title">American Anglossic Compass</h2>
            </div>
            <button class="button-secondary" id="compass-close" type="button">Close</button>
          </div>
          <div class="lab-controls">
            <button class="lab-button" id="compass-prev" type="button">Previous</button>
            <button class="lab-button" id="compass-hold" type="button">Hold prompt</button>
            <button class="lab-button" id="compass-next" type="button">Next unanswered</button>
            <button class="lab-button" id="compass-reset" type="button">Start over</button>
          </div>
          <div class="lab-layout">
            <section class="stack">
              <div class="card" id="compass-progress" aria-live="polite"></div>
              <div class="card" id="compass-question"></div>
              <div class="card" id="compass-results" aria-live="polite" hidden></div>
            </section>
            <aside class="stack">
              <section class="card">
                <h3 class="section-heading">Held prompts</h3>
                <div class="lab-skipped" id="compass-held"></div>
              </section>
              <section class="card">
                <h3 class="section-heading">Question map</h3>
                <div class="lab-index" id="compass-index"></div>
              </section>
            </aside>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="lab-modal" id="compass-gate" hidden>
      <div class="card lab-dialog" id="compass-gate-dialog" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="compass-gate-title" tabindex="-1">
        <div class="stack">
          <div>
            <p class="page-intro__kicker">Reading access</p>
            <h2 class="section-heading" id="compass-gate-title">Open the result reading</h2>
            <p class="section-copy">Leave an email to save your place on the updates list, or continue without it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="compass-gate-email">Email for this reading</label>
            <input class="input" id="compass-gate-email" type="email" autocomplete="email" placeholder="your@email.com" />
          </div>
          <div class="actions">
            <button class="button" id="compass-gate-submit" type="button">Open the reading</button>
            <button class="button-secondary" id="compass-gate-skip" type="button">Continue without email</button>
            <button class="button-secondary" id="compass-gate-close" type="button">Not now</button>
          </div>
          <div class="status-panel" id="compass-gate-helper" role="status" aria-live="polite" hidden>
            <div data-status-text></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="scripts">
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/site-shell.js" type="module"></script>
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/lab-anglossic-entry.js" type="module"></script>
  </Fragment>
</Base>
